user.biography:
Welcome to the Salone del Mobile.Milano official Instagram profile.
The special event #supersalone21 will be held from 5th to 10th September 2021

node.text:
Il meglio dell'evoluzione del design e freneticamente accogliente. Di cosa stiamo parlando? Scopritelo nel nuovo video in collaborazione con @skytg24 con protagonisti @davideoldani @enricobertolino_ @stefano_boeri @claudia_segre 
#Salonedelmobile2021

node.text:
We won't stop. We can't stop. Salone del Mobile.Milano will be held from 16th to 21st June at Rho Fiera Milano, hear @BeppeSala, Mayor of #Milano, to know more
#SaloneDelMobile #SaloneDelMobile2020 #iSaloni #Eurocucina #SaloneDelBagno #ClaudioLuti #EmanueleOrsini

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 29, 2021 tagging @arper_official, and @lievore_altherrdesilepark. May be an image of furniture.

node.text: Kata is Arper’s first lounge chair, fitting seamlessly into its surroundings and, while evoking traditional codes, is outward-looking, new and effervescent, expressing all its character and originality to the full. Read more in the article by Marilena Sobacchi, link in bio #closeup #salonedelmobile

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 27, 2021 tagging @franpesca___, and @flexformspa. May be an image of 1 person, sitting, sunglasses, wrist watch, outdoors and text.

node.text: The new products in the collection in September, the digital revolution, a new way of looking at the home, and 160 employees who represent the core strength of the company. Read more in the interview with Matteo Galimberti, CEO of @flexformspa, by @franpesca___, link in bio #speakerscorner #salonedelmobile

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 27, 2021 tagging @franpesca___, and @flexformspa. May be an image of 1 person, sitting, sunglasses, wrist watch, outdoors and text.

Photo by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 27, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'That relationship, the one that is created with people, is unique, rare and almost impossible to recapture without the Salone del Mobile. MATTEO GALIMBERTI'.
Photo shared by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 26, 2021 tagging @studioolafureliasson, and @fondationbeyeler. May be an image of one or more people, tree and outdoors.

node.text: We’ve chosen seven exhibitions showing at some of Europe’s leading cultural institutions, in which contemporary architects, designers and artists reflect on contemporary environmental issues. Read more in the #greenreport by @salvatore.pel, link in bio #salonedelmobile

#SaloneDelMobile

node.text: Poetic and ironic, Giovanni del Vecchio, CEO of @giorgettiofficial, counts down to the “supersalone”. Amidst memories and analysis, news and emotions, a long-awaited return for the Brianza-based company founded 123 years ago. Read more in the interview by @franpesca___, link in bio #speakerscorner #salonedelmobile

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 23, 2021 tagging @franpesca___, and @giorgettiofficial. May be an image of 1 person, suit and text that says 'GIOVANNI DEL VECCHIO'.

Photo by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 23, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'Design is poetry first and foremost. Functionality, in the end, can be replaced. GIOVANNI DEL VECCHIO'.
Photo shared by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 22, 2021 tagging @kartell_official, and @adidesignmuseum.

node.text: A tribute to a true pioneer of Italian design, a person who used plastic to revolutionise the world of furniture and the home. Read more about Giulio Castelli in the article by Patrizia Malfatti link in bio #salonedelmobile

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 22, 2021 tagging @kartell_official, and @adidesignmuseum.

Photo by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 22, 2021.

node.text: A standard-bearer for Belgian design, he’s a born designer and loves biology. His latest creation: a sculptural and functional whale/cabinet, designed especially to trigger a mass of positive emotions. Read more about @xavierlust in the article by @mcdidero, link in bio #salonedelmobile

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 21, 2021 tagging @xavierlust, and @mcdidero.

Photo by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 21, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'As a child, I was interested in finding out and understanding how and why things existed. As a rule, I try to keep the same open mind and curiosity. XAVIER LUST'.
Photo by Salone del Mobile.Milano on July 20, 2021. May be a closeup of 1 person.

node.text: “Our goal is a strong, united, inclusive, sustainable and creative Salone del Mobile,” says Maria Porro, newly-elected President of the Salone del Mobile.Milano, read more in the link in bio. Photo by @giovanni_gastel #mariaporro #thevoiceofsalone #salonedelmobile

node.text: Will the digital migration we are witnessing lead to an immaterial future? Alexandre Humbert from @studio_alexandrehumbert, designer-filmmaker with a philosophical attitude, wonders. Read more in the article by Marianna Guernieri, link in bio #salonedelmobile
